                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2000-10-29</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>The author definitely did extensive research into COM+ when writing this book. Every page is packed of insightful information and valueable guide to use COM+ EFFECTIVELY. If you are a developer using COM components, this book will sure to broaden your understanding into COM and get your skill up to date with COM+. Sure there are other books out there on VB & COM, but I have yet to across one that is as well written as this one. Many reviewers said they read the book more than once. It's not because the book is hard to understand, it is because they didn't want to miss out anything.</span>
                  
