                    <span>I have huge respect for the author and the knowledge shared with us in this book. I love the aspect of "WHY is this the way it is?" for every chapter in the book. I would rather know first how things work beehind the scenes so I can then develop against that knowledge. This is definitely for someone with at least 2-3yrs of good experience with VB6 and MTS. I was able to step one level up in COM+ architecture and become advanced programmer/architect just by finishing this book. Excellent!</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">He knows his stuff...</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
